content:
Below is a **single‑file** (self‑contained) HTML page.  
Open it in a browser, click the button, and a random joke (out of the four you provide) will appear.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Random Joke Generator</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      padding: 2rem;
      background: #f0f8ff;
      text-align: center;
    }
    #jokeBtn {
      padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
      font-size: 1rem;
      cursor: pointer;
    }
    #jokeDisplay {
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      color: #333;
      min-height: 2rem;          /* keep space for the joke */
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <h1>Want a laugh?</h1>

  <button id="jokeBtn">Tell me a joke!</button>

  <p id="jokeDisplay"></p>

  <script>
    // --- Joke data ---------------------------------------
    const jokes = [
      "Why don’t scientists trust atoms? Because they make up everything!",
      "I told my wife she was drawing her eyebrows too high. She looked surprised.",
      "What do you call a fake noodle? An impasta!",
      "I’m reading a book on anti‑gravity. It’s impossible to put down!"
    ];

    // --- Utility function ---------------------------------
    /**
     * Pick a random item from an array
     * @param {Array} arr
     * @returns {any} Random element
     */
    function getRandom(arr) {
      return arr[Math.floor(Math.random() * arr.length)];
    }

    // --- Event handling -----------------------------------
    const button = document.getElementById('jokeBtn');
    const display = document.getElementById('jokeDisplay');

    button.addEventListener('click', () => {
      display.textContent = getRandom(jokes);
    });
  </script>

</body>
</html>
```

### How it works
1. **Array of jokes** – The four jokes are stored in the `jokes` array.  
2. **Random selection** – The helper `getRandom()` returns a random element from the array.  
3. **Button click** – When the button is clicked, the `click` event handler calls `getRandom(jokes)` and shows the result in the paragraph with id `jokeDisplay`.

Feel free to add more jokes to the array or tweak the styling as you like!
